00:20:39,217 --> 00:20:40,635
You usually come along secretly

424
00:20:40,635 --> 00:20:42,335
and ask them without asking for permission.

425
00:20:42,335 --> 00:20:44,535
Well, you see...

426
00:20:44,535 --> 00:20:46,035
What is it?

427
00:20:48,435 --> 00:20:52,635
What? Genta's father is among the three?

428
00:20:52,635 --> 00:20:54,435
Which... which one is he?

429
00:20:54,435 --> 00:20:57,235
I don't know because I've never met him.

430
00:20:57,235 --> 00:21:02,135
Maybe he knows me by photos or something, though.

431
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:04,735
Then, I can find out right away if I ask.

432
00:21:04,735 --> 00:21:06,135
I'll talk to Inspector Megure

433
00:21:06,135 --> 00:21:07,935
and have him taken off the list of suspects.

434
00:21:07,935 --> 00:21:10,535
No! Holmes also said,

435
00:21:10,535 --> 00:21:12,335
"Emotional qualities at times

436
00:21:12,335 --> 00:21:16,535
can interfere deduction carrying you away from the truth".

437
00:21:16,535 --> 00:21:18,135
We can't be 100% sure that he's not a suspect

438
00:21:18,135 --> 00:21:21,735
just because he's Genta's father, can we?

439
00:21:21,735 --> 00:21:23,535
If you want to make a composed deduction,

